node.text:
I said it once, and ill repeat it: arguing is the lowest form of communication.

What we want is to be heard, to enter safe forms of communication, and to share how we think and feel. We have to let go of arguing and replace it with listening and collaboration.

Arguing as a vessel does not get you there? Unless you get paid to go on TV and argue, there's no reason to use that tactic in real life. Listen all thriugh on this one for some solid techniques and practices.

There's 9 days left until my Art Of Letting Go workshop starts where you'll learn all about “How To Let Go”. Visit the link in my bio or iamlettinggo.net to get your spot! You dont want to miss this workshop. 

#SylvesterMcNutt

Drop a comment below and let me know what your thoughts are! 

Workshop Alert: 9 days left until The Art Of Letting Go workshop happens!! On August 13th, I'm doing an immersive deep dive into the subject of letting go. 

I'll teach you how to let go and how to enable the peace of mind you deserve. Go to the link in my bio and reserve your spot in "The Art Of Letting Go Workshop."

node.text:
What a fun chat on identity. Thank you to everyone who joined me live here on Instagram. 

Here’s the structure of the chat: 

• the question I’m curious about answering
• an explanation of lower and higher vibrations
• an explanation of genuine self-compassion
• step one
• step two
• step three
• summary

node.text:
The first step towards letting go is giving up the obsessive chase to be liked, agreed with, accepted, validated. It's fantastic when we find agreement and when we are validated, that is good for everyone. However, we have to make sure we are not self-abandoning for "approval".

That in itself gives you a great deal of freedom and reign to live your most authentic self.

Comment below and let me know what your thoughts are! 

On August 13th, I'm doing an immersive deep dive into the subject of letting go. I'll teach you how to let go and how to enable the peace of mind you deserve. Go to the link in my bio and reserve your spot in "The Art Of Letting Go Workshop."

node.title: Letting Go: Let Go Of Other People's Approval

node.text:
Speak good energy and life into yourself every single day. Always use self-compasdion when you talk about your journey. As a consequence of self-compassion, your vibration will change. As a consequence of a raised vibration, you'll find it easier to set boundaries.

I'm going live tomorrow on Instagram. Send me your questions or topics you’d like me to cover via direct message. Turn on my post notifications, so you don't miss when I go live!

node.title: How Do I Speak Up For Myself

node.text:
This clip is from a mini-episode of the Free Your Energy podcast. Grab it on Spotify or iTunes.

If you enjoy long-form podcasts, you'll love hearing me jam with world-class teachers, storytellers, and people with immense passion.

During the week, I do mini-episodes on different topics that inspire me!  If you NEED more words on overthinking, I have a mini-course called “How To Stop Overthinking.” You can grab that from Sylvestermcnutt.net/courses

I hope you get into the activity, action, and into the mud! It's the only way to create what you're envisioning!

node.text:
LAST CHANCE: the Art Of Letting Go workshop is in 6 hours. Register now via the link in my bio. You don't want to miss this immersive deep dive into the subject of letting go.

I’ll teach you how to let go and how to enable the peace of mind you deserve. I’ll teach you how to recognize peace, and relinquish some of the threads that we hold on too yo tightly. 

(If you can’t make it live but you register you WILL get access to ALL of the content after my team edit’s it! Go get your spot now!)

Go to the link in my bio and reserve your spot in “The Art Of Letting Go Workshop.” I won’t teach this workshop again until the fall! See you in a few hours!

node.text:
The past is the past — do you have the capacity to honor and respect it? I've found healing, peace of mind, and new possibility by finding a complete acceptance of the past (without shame).

There's a lot available to us in the present moment, but we must choose to be objective observers. Is it possible that focusing on the present moment can bring you clarity and purpose?

When we speak on the past, we may relive those emotions, and we may reinforce a story. Please, be mindful of the story you are telling yourself.

Alert: I’m teaching a powerful workshop in seven days. It’s called The Art Of Letting Go. I’m going to teach you HOW to let go. Visit the link in my bio or go to Iamlettinggo.net and register. There are 90 spots left for this before we close the cart.

node.text:
I said it once, and ill repeat it: arguing is the lowest form of communication.

What we want is to be heard, to enter safe forms of communication, and to share how we think and feel. We have to let go of arguing and replace it with listening and collaboration.

Arguing as a vessel does not get you there? Unless you get paid to go on TV and argue, there's no reason to use that tactic in real life. Listen all thriugh on this one for some solid techniques and practices.

There's 9 days left until my Art Of Letting Go workshop starts where you'll learn all about “How To Let Go”. Visit the link in my bio or iamlettinggo.net to get your spot! You dont want to miss this workshop. 

#SylvesterMcNutt

node.text:
Living in the future creates the perfect landscape for worry, anxiety, and constant comparison to thrive (is that what we want)? There is nothing 'wrong' with these emotions; however, triggering them when we don't need to use them can lower our vibration ( and more depending on the person). ⁠
⁠
What I find extremely helpful towards staying present is fitness training, reading daily for ten to twenty minutes, daily mediation, and journaling. Becoming more present allows us to focus intensely on what we love, what matters, and it gives us the landscape to vibrate in the frequency of gratitude ( a high vibration).⁠
⁠
Another excellent healing modality that I love is going for an hour walk. I don't enjoy those in the summer here in Arizona, ha, but I'm privileged enough to access meditation, journaling, and the other things I mentioned. What do you have access to that allows you to practice presence?⁠
⁠
Now, there's a practical side of thinking in the future because that's how we set goals, make plans, and give ourselves targets. I don't believe that neglecting those things under the name of presence is the way; there's a beautiful balance there. And that's all the body wants, right –– is the balance? ⁠
⁠
Comment below and let me know what your relationship is with being and practicing presence? Do you need to let go of obsessive future thoughts? Do you have a good balance? Are you too present and don't plan enough? With love, ⁠
⁠
#SylvesterMcNutt ⁠
⁠
